name: Breaking Bad
details: A high school chemistry teacher diagnosed with inoperable lung cancer turns to manufacturing and selling methamphetamine in order to secure his family's future.

name: Game of Thrones
details: Nine noble families fight for control over the lands of Westeros, while an ancient enemy returns after being dormant for millennia.

name: Chernobyl
details: In April 1986, an explosion at the Chernobyl nuclear power plant in the Union of Soviet Socialist Republics becomes one of the world's worst man-made catastrophes.

name: Band of Brothers
details: The story of Easy Company of the U.S. Army 101st Airborne Division and their mission in World War II Europe, from Operation Overlord to V-J Day.

name: Sherlock
details: A modern update finds the famous sleuth and his doctor partner solving crime in 21st century London.

name: Rick and Morty
details: An animated series that follows the exploits of a super scientist and his not-so-bright grandson.

name: The Wire
details: The Baltimore drug scene, as seen through the eyes of drug dealers and law enforcement.

name: Avatar: The Last Airbender
details: In a war-torn world of elemental magic, a young boy reawakens to undertake a dangerous mystic quest to fulfill his destiny as the Avatar, and bring peace to the world.

name: The Sopranos
details: New Jersey mob boss Tony Soprano deals with personal and professional issues in his home and business life that affect his mental state, leading him to seek professional psychiatric counseling.

name: Friends
details: Follows the personal and professional lives of six twenty to thirty-something-year-old friends living in Manhattan.

name: True Detective
details: Seasonal anthology series in which police investigations unearth the personal and professional secrets of those involved, both within and outside the law.

name: Stranger Things
details: When a young boy disappears, his mother, a police chief and his friends must confront terrifying supernatural forces in order to get him back.

name: The Office
details: A mockumentary on a group of typical office workers, where the workday consists of ego clashes, inappropriate behavior, and tedium.

name: Death Note
details: An intelligent high school student goes on a secret crusade to eliminate criminals from the world after discovering a notebook capable of killing anyone whose name is written into it.

name: Black Mirror
details: An anthology series exploring a twisted, high-tech multiverse where humanity's greatest innovations and darkest instincts collide.

name: Fargo
details: Various chronicles of deception, intrigue and murder in and around frozen Minnesota. Yet all of these tales mysteriously lead back one way or another to Fargo, North Dakota.

name: Attack on Titan
details: After his hometown is destroyed and his mother is killed, young Eren Jaeger vows to cleanse the earth of the giant humanoid Titans that have brought humanity to the brink of extinction.

name: Firefly
details: Five hundred years in the future, a renegade crew aboard a small spacecraft tries to survive as they travel the unknown parts of the galaxy and evade warring factions as well as authority agents out to get them.

name: Peaky Blinders
details: A gangster family epic set in 1900s England, centering on a gang who sew razor blades in the peaks of their caps, and their fierce boss Tommy Shelby.

name: Narcos
details: A chronicled look at the criminal exploits of Colombian drug lord Pablo Escobar, as well as the many other drug kingpins who plagued the country through the years.

name: Dexter
details: He's smart. He's lovable. He's Dexter Morgan, America's favorite serial killer, who spends his days solving crimes and nights committing them. Golden Globe winner Michael C. Hall stars in the hit SHOWTIME Original Series.

name: The Mandalorian
details: The travels of a lone bounty hunter in the outer reaches of the galaxy, far from the authority of the New Republic.

name: Better Call Saul
details: The trials and tribulations of criminal lawyer Jimmy McGill in the time before he established his strip-mall law office in Albuquerque, New Mexico.

name: House of Cards
details: A Congressman works with his equally conniving wife to exact revenge on the people who betrayed him.

name: Dark
details: A family saga with a supernatural twist, set in a German town, where the disappearance of two young children exposes the relationships among four families.

name: Fullmetal Alchemist: Brotherhood
details: Two brothers search for a Philosopher's Stone after an attempt to revive their deceased mother goes awry and leaves them in damaged physical forms.

name: House
details: An antisocial maverick doctor who specializes in diagnostic medicine does whatever it takes to solve puzzling cases that come his way using his crack team of doctors and his wits.

name: Arcane
details: Set in utopian Piltover and the oppressed underground of Zaun, the story follows the origins of two iconic League champions-and the power that will tear them apart.

name: Seinfeld
details: The continuing misadventures of neurotic New York City stand-up comedian Jerry Seinfeld and his equally neurotic New York City friends.

name: South Park
details: Follows the misadventures of four irreverent grade-schoolers in the quiet, dysfunctional town of South Park, Colorado.

name: Westworld
details: Set at the intersection of the near future and the reimagined past, explore a world in which every human appetite can be indulged without consequence.

name: The Boys
details: A group of vigilantes set out to take down corrupt superheroes who abuse their superpowers.

name: Arrested Development
details: Level-headed son Michael Bluth takes over family affairs after his father is imprisoned. But the rest of his spoiled, dysfunctional family are making his job unbearable.

name: Daredevil
details: A blind lawyer by day, vigilante by night. Matt Murdock fights the crime of New York as Daredevil.

name: The Simpsons
details: The satiric adventures of a working-class family in the misfit city of Springfield.

name: The Queen's Gambit
details: Orphaned at the tender age of nine, prodigious introvert Beth Harmon discovers and masters the game of chess in 1960s USA. But child stardom comes at a price.

name: It's Always Sunny in Philadelphia
details: Five friends with big egos and small brains are the proprietors of an Irish pub in Philadelphia.

name: Vikings

name: Twin Peaks
details: An idiosyncratic FBI agent investigates the murder of a young woman in the even more idiosyncratic town of Twin Peaks.

name: Batman: The Animated Series
details: The Dark Knight battles crime in Gotham City with occasional help from Robin and Batgirl.

name: Mr. Robot

name: The Walking Dead
details: Sheriff Deputy Rick Grimes wakes up from a coma to learn the world is in ruins and must lead a group of survivors to stay alive.

name: How I Met Your Mother
details: A father recounts to his children - through a series of flashbacks - the journey he and his four best friends took leading up to him meeting their mother.

name: Mindhunter
details: Set in the late 1970s, two FBI agents are tasked with interviewing serial killers to solve open cases.

name: Downton Abbey
details: A chronicle of the lives of the British aristocratic Crawley family and their servants in the early twentieth century.

name: When They See Us
details: Five teens from Harlem become trapped in a nightmare when they're falsely accused of a brutal attack in Central Park. Based on the true story.

name: Ted Lasso
details: American college football coach Ted Lasso heads to London to manage AFC Richmond, a struggling English Premier League soccer team.

name: One Punch Man
details: The story of Saitama, a hero that does it just for fun & can defeat his enemies with a single punch.

name: Parks and Recreation
details: The absurd antics of an Indiana town's public officials as they pursue sundry projects to make their city a better place.

name: Cowboy Bebop
details: The futuristic misadventures and tragedies of an easygoing bounty hunter and his partners.

name: Supernatural
details: Two brothers follow their father's footsteps as hunters, fighting evil supernatural beings of many kinds, including monsters, demons and gods that roam the earth.

name: The Twilight Zone
details: Ordinary people find themselves in extraordinarily astounding situations, which they each try to solve in a remarkable manner.

name: Mad Men
details: A drama about one of New York's most prestigious ad agencies at the beginning of the 1960s, focusing on one of the firm's most mysterious but extremely talented ad executives, Donald Draper.

name: Hunter x Hunter
details: Gon Freecss aspires to become a Hunter, an exceptional being capable of greatness. With his friends and his potential, he seeks for his father who left him when he was younger.

name: Modern Family
details: Three different but related families face trials and tribulations in their own uniquely comedic ways.

name: Rome
details: A down-to-earth account of the lives of both illustrious and ordinary Romans set in the last days of the Roman Republic.

name: The Haunting of Hill House
details: Flashing between past and present, a fractured family confronts haunting memories of their old home and the terrifying events that drove them from it.

name: Suits
details: On the run from a drug deal gone bad, brilliant college dropout Mike Ross finds himself working with Harvey Specter, one of New York City's best lawyers.

name: Lost
details: The survivors of a plane crash are forced to work together in order to survive on a seemingly deserted tropical island.

name: The X-Files
details: Two F.B.I. Agents, Fox Mulder the believer and Dana Scully the skeptic, investigate the strange and unexplained, while hidden forces work to impede their efforts.

name: Battlestar Galactica
details: When an old enemy, the Cylons, resurface and obliterate the 12 colonies, the crew of the aged Galactica protect a small civilian fleet - the last of humanity - as they journey toward the fabled 13th colony, Earth.

name: Doctor Who
details: The further adventures in time and space of the alien adventurer known as the Doctor and their companions from planet Earth.

name: Sons of Anarchy
details: A biker struggles to balance being a father and being involved in an outlaw motorcycle club.

name: Prison Break
details: Due to a political conspiracy, an innocent man is sent to death row and his only hope is his brother, who makes it his mission to deliberately get himself sent to the same prison in order to break the both of them out, from the inside.

name: Gravity Falls
details: Twin siblings Dipper and Mabel Pines spend the summer at their great-uncle's tourist trap in the enigmatic Gravity Falls, Oregon.

name: Hannibal
details: Explores the early relationship between renowned psychiatrist Hannibal Lecter and a young FBI criminal profiler who is haunted by his ability to empathize with serial killers.

name: Community
details: A suspended lawyer is forced to enroll in a community college with an eccentric staff and student body.

name: The Crown
details: Follows the political rivalries and romance of Queen Elizabeth II's reign and the events that shaped the second half of the twentieth century.

name: Freaks and Geeks
details: A high school mathlete starts hanging out with a group of burnouts while her younger brother navigates his freshman year.

name: BoJack Horseman
details: BoJack Horseman was the star of the hit television show "Horsin' Around" in the '80s and '90s, but now he's washed up, living in Hollywood, complaining about everything, and wearing colorful sweaters.

name: Spartacus

name: Six Feet Under

name: Shameless
details: A scrappy, feisty, fiercely loyal Chicago family makes no apologies.

name: Fleabag
details: A comedy series adapted from the award-winning play about a young woman trying to cope with life in London whilst coming to terms with a recent tragedy.

name: The Big Bang Theory
details: A woman who moves into an apartment across the hall from two brilliant but socially awkward physicists shows them how little they know about life outside of the laboratory.

name: Dragon Ball Z
details: After learning that he is from another planet, a warrior named Goku and his friends are prompted to defend it from an onslaught of extraterrestrial enemies.

name: The Punisher
details: After the murder of his family, Marine veteran Frank Castle becomes the vigilante known as "The Punisher," with only one goal in mind: to avenge them.

name: Brooklyn Nine-Nine
details: Comedy series following the exploits of Det. Jake Peralta and his diverse, lovable colleagues as they police the NYPD's 99th Precinct.

name: One Piece
details: Follows the adventures of Monkey D. Luffy and his pirate crew in order to find the greatest treasure ever left by the legendary Pirate, Gold Roger. The famous mystery treasure named "One Piece".

name: Curb Your Enthusiasm
details: The life and times of  and the predicaments he gets himself into with his friends and complete strangers.

name: Archer
details: Covert black ops and espionage take a back seat to zany personalities and relationships between secret agents and drones.

name: Homeland
details: A bipolar CIA operative becomes convinced a prisoner of war has been turned by al-Qaeda and is planning to carry out a terrorist attack on American soil.

name: Pride and Prejudice
details: While the arrival of wealthy gentlemen sends her marriage-minded mother into a frenzy, willful and opinionated Elizabeth Bennet matches wits with haughty Mr. Darcy.

name: Boardwalk Empire

name: Big Little Lies
details: The apparently perfect lives of upper-class mothers, at a prestigious elementary school, unravel to the point of murder when a single-mother moves to their quaint Californian beach town.

name: Fringe
details: An F.B.I. agent is forced to work with an institutionalized scientist and his son in order to rationalize a brewing storm of unexplained phenomena.

name: Cobra Kai
details: Decades after their 1984 All Valley Karate Tournament bout, a middle-aged Daniel LaRusso and Johnny Lawrence find themselves martial-arts rivals again.

name: Persona
details: A man diagnosed with Alzheimer's decides to punish criminals.

name: Futurama
details: Philip J. Fry, a pizza delivery boy, is accidentally frozen in 1999 and thawed out on New Year's Eve 2999.

name: Invincible
details: An adult animated series based on the Skybound/Image comic about a teenager whose father is the most powerful superhero on the planet.

name: Money Heist
details: An unusual group of robbers attempt to carry out the most perfect robbery in Spanish history - stealing 2.4 billion euros from the Royal Mint of Spain.

name: Ozark
details: A financial advisor drags his family from Chicago to the Missouri Ozarks, where he must launder money to appease a drug boss.

name: Oz
details: A series chronicling the daily activities of an unusual prison facility and its criminal inhabitants.

name: The Marvelous Mrs. Maisel
details: A housewife in 1958 decides to become a stand-up comic.

name: This Is Us
details: A heartwarming and emotional story about a unique set of triplets, their struggles and their wonderful parents.

name: The West Wing
details: Inside the lives of staffers in the West Wing of the White House.

name: The Handmaid's Tale
details: Set in a dystopian future, a woman is forced to live as a concubine under a fundamentalist theocratic dictatorship.

name: Fawlty Towers
details: Hotel owner Basil Fawlty's incompetence, short fuse, and arrogance form a combination that ensures accidents and trouble are never far away.

name: The Witcher

name: Star Trek: The Next Generation

name: The Newsroom

name: The IT Crowd

name: Succession

name: Only Fools and Horses

name: Scrubs
details: In the unreal world of Sacred Heart Hospital, intern John "J.D." Dorian learns the ways of medicine, friendship and life.

name: Silicon Valley

name: The Night Of
details: After a night of partying with a woman he picked up, a man wakes up to find her stabbed to death and is charged with her murder.

name: Naruto: Shippûden

name: Sex Education

name: Spartacus: Gods of the Arena
details: In the time before the arrival of Spartacus, the House of Batiatus faces many challenges from competitors, and within its own household.

name: Deadwood

name: The Shield

name: Person of Interest

name: Loki
details: The mercurial villain Loki resumes his role as the God of Mischief in a new series that takes place after the events of “Avengers: Endgame.”

name: Love, Death & Robots
details: A collection of animated short stories that span various genres including science fiction, fantasy, horror and comedy.

name: The Expanse
details: In the 24th century, a group of humans untangle a vast plot which threatens the Solar System's fragile state of detente.

name: Entourage
details: Film star Vince Chase navigates the vapid terrain of Los Angeles with a close circle of friends and his trusty agent.

name: Justified
details: U.S. Marshal Raylan Givens is reassigned from Miami to his childhood home in the poor, rural coal mining towns of eastern Kentucky.

name: Mare of Easttown
details: A detective in a small Pennsylvania town investigates a local murder while trying to keep her life from falling apart.

name: Steins;Gate
details: After discovering time travel, a university student and his colleagues must use their knowledge of it to stop an evil organization and their diabolical plans.

name: Adventure Time
details: A 12-year-old boy and his best friend, wise 28-year-old dog with magical powers, go on a series of surreal adventures with each other in a remote future.

name: Blackadder Goes Forth
details: Stuck in the middle of World War I, Captain Edmund Blackadder does his best to escape the banality of the war.

name: Sacred Games
details: A link in their pasts leads an honest cop to a fugitive gang boss, whose cryptic warning spurs the officer on a quest to save Mumbai from cataclysm.

name: Outlander
details: An English combat nurse from 1945 is mysteriously swept back in time to 1743.

name: Yellowstone
details: A ranching family in Montana faces off against others encroaching on their land.

name: The Office
details: The story of an office that faces closure when the company decides to downsize its branches. A documentary film crew follow staff and the manager David Brent as they continue their daily lives.

name: Over the Garden Wall
details: Two brothers find themselves lost in a mysterious land and try to find their way home.
Jack Bauer races against the clock to subvert terrorist plots and save his nation from ultimate disaster.

name: Schitt's Creek
details: When rich video-store magnate Johnny Rose and his family suddenly find themselves broke, they are forced to leave their pampered lives to regroup in Schitt's Creek.

name: Squid Game

name: Californication
details: A writer tries to juggle his career, his relationship with his daughter and his ex-girlfriend, as well as his appetite for beautiful women.

name: Code Geass
details: After being given a mysterious power to control others, an outcast prince becomes the masked leader of the rebellion against an all powerful empire

name: Family Guy
details: In a wacky Rhode Island town, a dysfunctional family strive to cope with everyday life as they are thrown from one crazy scenario to another.

name: Luther
details: DCI John Luther is a near-genius murder detective whose brilliant mind can't always save him from the dangerous violence of his passions.

details: A family is attacked by demons and only two members survive - Tanjiro and his sister Nezuko, who is turning into a demon slowly. Tanjiro sets out to become a demon slayer to avenge his family and cure his sister.

name: Battlestar Galactica

name: Taboo

name: The Legend of Korra

name: Line of Duty
details: Drama series following the investigations of AC-12, a controversial police anti-corruption unit.

name: Sense8
details: A group of people around the world are suddenly linked mentally, and must find a way to survive being hunted by those who see them as a threat to the world's order.

name: The Bridge

name: Dekalog
details: Ten television drama films, each one based on one of the Ten Commandments.

name: Friday Night Lights
details: A drama that follows the lives of the Dillon Panthers, one of the nation's best high school football teams, and their head coach Eric Taylor.

name: Broadchurch
details: The murder of a young boy in a small coastal town brings a media frenzy, which threatens to tear the community apart.

name: Anne with an E

name: Atlanta

name: Louie
details: The life of Louie C.K., a divorced comedian living in New York with two kids.

name: The Last Kingdom
details: As Alfred the Great defends his kingdom from Norse invaders, Uhtred - born a Saxon but raised by Vikings - seeks to claim his ancestral birthright.

name: After Life

name: Peep Show

name: What We Do in the Shadows

name: Banshee

name: American Horror Story

name: The Americans

name: American Crime Story
details: An anthology series centered around America's most notorious crimes and criminals.

name: Orange Is the New Black

name: Stargate SG-1

name: Unbelievable

name: Fullmetal Alchemist

name: The Inbetweeners
details: Follows four friends and their antics during their final years of school.

name: Billions
details: U.S. Attorney Chuck Rhoades goes after hedge fund king Bobby "Axe" Axelrod in a battle between two powerful New York figures.

name: Euphoria
details: A look at life for a group of high school students as they grapple with issues of drugs, sex, and violence.

name: Twin Peaks
details: Picks up 25 years after the inhabitants of a quaint northwestern town are stunned when their homecoming queen is murdered.

name: Orphan Black

name: The Pacific
details: The Pacific Theatre of World War II, as seen through the eyes of several young Marines.

name: Buffy the Vampire Slayer
details: A young woman, destined to slay vampires, demons and other infernal creatures, deals with her life fighting evil, with the help of her friends.

name: The Good Place
details: Four people and their otherworldly frienemy struggle in the afterlife to define what it means to be good.

name: Neon Genesis Evangelion
details: A teenage boy finds himself recruited as a member of an elite team of pilots by his father.

name: Criminal Minds
details: The cases of the F.B.I. Behavioral Analysis Unit (B.A.U.), an elite group of profilers who analyze the nation's most dangerous serial killers and individual heinous crimes in an effort to anticipate their next moves before they strike again.

name: WandaVision

name: Das Boot
details: A World War II German U-Boat crew have a terrifying patrol mission in the early days of the war.

name: Chuck

name: The Mentalist

name: Narcos: Mexico

name: Black Books

name: The Originals

name: Jujutsu Kaisen

name: White Collar

name: Gomorrah

name: The End of the F***ing World

name: The Blacklist

name: Berserk

name: Psych

name: Poirot
details: The cases of eccentric, but sharp, Belgian detective Hercule Poirot.

name: Ash vs Evil Dead

name: Spaced

name: The Leftovers

name: 30 Rock

name: Penny Dreadful

name: Normal People

name: Generation Kill

name: Maid
details: After fleeing an abusive relationship, a young mother finds a job cleaning houses as she fights to provide for her child and build them a better future.

name: Naruto
details: Naruto Uzumaki, a mischievous adolescent ninja, struggles as he searches for recognition and dreams of becoming the Hokage, the village's leader and strongest ninja.

name: Castle
details: After a serial killer imitates the plots of his novels, successful mystery novelist Richard "Rick" Castle receives permission from the Mayor of New York City to tag along with an NYPD homicide investigation team for research purposes.

name: Vinland Saga
details: Thorfinn pursues a journey with his father's killer in order to take revenge and end his life in a duel as an honorable warrior and pay his father a homage.

name: Gilmore Girls
details: A dramedy centering around the relationship between a thirtysomething single mother and her teen daughter living in Stars Hollow, Connecticut.

name: Samurai Jack
details: A samurai, sent through time, fights to return home and save the world.

name: Father Ted
details: Three misfit priests and their housekeeper live on Craggy Island, not the peaceful and quiet part of Ireland that it seems to be.

name: The Morning Show
details: An inside look at the lives of the people who help America wake up in the morning, exploring the unique challenges faced by the men and women who carry out this daily televised ritual.

name: Ray Donovan
details: Ray Donovan, a professional "fixer" for the rich and famous in Los Angeles, can make anyone's problems disappear except those created by his own family.

name: Watchmen
details: Set in an alternate history where masked vigilantes are treated as outlaws, Watchmen embraces the nostalgia of the original groundbreaking graphic novel of the same name, while attempting to break new ground of its own.

name: How to Get Away with Murder
details: A group of ambitious law students and their brilliant criminal defense professor become involved in a twisted murder plot that promises to change the course of their lives.

name: The Killing
details: A police investigation, the saga of a grieving family, and a Seattle mayoral campaign all interlock after the body of 17-year-old Rosie Larsen is found in the trunk of a submerged car.

name: The Umbrella Academy
details: A family of former child heroes, now grown apart, must reunite to continue to protect the world.

name: Atypical
details: Sam, an 18-year-old on the autism spectrum, decides it's time to find a girlfriend, a journey that sets Sam's mom on her own life-changing path as her son seeks more independence.

name: Star Trek: The Original Series
details: In the 23rd Century, Captain James T. Kirk and the crew of the U.S.S. Enterprise explore the galaxy and defend the United Federation of Planets.

name: Young Justice
details: Teenage superheroes strive to prove themselves as members of the Justice League.

name: The Knick
details: A look at the professional and personal lives of the staff at New York's Knickerbocker Hospital during the early part of the twentieth century.

name: Bosch
details: An L.A.P.D. homicide detective works to solve the murder of a thirteen-year-old boy while standing trial in federal court for the murder of a serial killer.

name: Dexter: New Blood
details: Set 10 years after Dexter Morgan went missing in the eye of Hurricane Laura, he is now living under an assumed name in Upstate New York, Iron Lake, far from his original home in Miami.

name: Star Wars: The Clone Wars
details: Jedi Knights lead the Grand Army of the Republic against the droid army of the Separatists.

name: Killing Eve
details: After a series of events, the lives of a security operative and an assassin become inextricably linked.

name: Samurai Champloo
details: Fuu, a waitress who works in a teahouse, rescues two master swordsmen, Mugen and Jin, from their execution to help her find the "samurai who smells of sunflowers."

name: Black Sails
details: Follows Captain Flint and his pirates twenty years prior to Robert Louis Stevenson's classic novel "Treasure Island."

name: Coupling
details: Six best friends talk about all aspects of sex and relationships on their never-ending quest to find true love.

name: Justice League
details: Seven of the most formidable heroes form arguably the most powerful team ever.

name: Misfits
details: A group of young offenders doing community service get struck by lightning during a storm, and begin to develop superpowers.

name: The Good Wife
details: Alicia Florrick (Julianna Margulies) has been a good wife to her husband, a former state's attorney. After a very humiliating sex and corruption scandal, he is behind bars. She must now provide for her family and returns to work as a litigator in a law firm.

name: Dr. Horrible's Sing-Along Blog
details: An aspiring supervillain must balance his career and his pursuit of a beautiful do-gooder.

name: Master of None
details: The personal and professional life of Dev, a 30-year-old actor in New York.

name: Veronica Mars
details: After her best friend is murdered, and her father is removed as county Sheriff, Veronica Mars dedicates her life to cracking the toughest mysteries in the affluent town of Neptune.

name: M*A*S*H
details: The staff of an Army hospital in the Korean War find that laughter is the best way to deal with their situation.

name: It's a Sin
details: A chronicle of four friends during a decade in which everything changed, including the rise of AIDS.

name: The Bugs Bunny Show
details: TV series featuring the classic Looney Tunes animated shorts.

name: SpongeBob SquarePants
details: The misadventures of a talking sea sponge who works at a fast food restaurant, attends a boating school, and lives in an underwater pineapple.

name: That '70s Show
details: A comedy revolving around a group of teenage friends, their mishaps, and their coming of age, set in 1970s Wisconsin.

name: Trailer Park Boys
details: Three petty felons have a documentary made about their life in a trailer park.

name: North & South
details: North and South is a four part adaptation of Elizabeth Gaskell's love story of Margaret Hale, a middle class southerner who is forced to move to the northern town of Milton.

name: Skam
details: The story of young teenagers and pupils on Hartvig Nissens upper secondary school in Oslo, and their troubles, scandals and everyday life. Each season is told from a different person's point of view.

name: Legion
details: David Haller is a troubled young man diagnosed as schizophrenic, but after a strange encounter, he discovers special powers that will change his life forever.

name: Altered Carbon
details: Set in a future where consciousness is digitized and stored, a prisoner returns to life in a new body and must solve a mind-bending murder to win his freedom.

name: My Hero Academia
details: A superhero-loving boy without any powers is determined to enroll in a prestigious hero academy and learn what it really means to be a hero.

name: Erased
details: 29-year-old Satoru Fujinuma is sent back in time 18 years to prevent the events leading to his mother's death, which began with a series of kidnappings while he was in 5th grade.

name: Jessica Jones
details: Following the tragic end of her brief superhero career, Jessica Jones tries to rebuild her life as a private investigator, dealing with cases involving people with remarkable abilities in New York City.

name: Bodyguard
details: A contemporary thriller featuring the Royalty and Specialist Protection Branch of London's Metropolitan Police Service.
A high school teacher travels back in time to prevent John F. Kennedy's assassination.

name: Skins
details: The story of a group of British teens who are trying to grow up and find love and happiness despite questionable parenting and teachers who more want to be friends (and lovers) rather than authority figures.

name: Regular Show
details: The daily surreal adventures of a blue jay and raccoon duo that attempt to deal with their mundane jobs as groundskeepers at the local park.

name: Godless
details: In the 1880s American West, murderous outlaw gang leader Frank Griffin hunts for ex-protege Roy Goode. Frank's chase leads him to La Belle, New Mexico--a town inhabited, after a mining disaster, almost entirely by women.

name: The Thick of It
details: Set in the corridors of power and spin, the Minister for Social Affairs is continually harassed by Number 10's policy enforcer and dependent on his not-so-reliable team of civil servants.

name: Bates Motel
details: A contemporary prequel to Psycho, giving a portrayal of how Norman Bates' psyche unravels through his teenage years, and how deeply intricate his relationship with his mother, Norma, truly is.

name: Tom Clancy's Jack Ryan
details: An up-and-coming CIA analyst, Jack Ryan, is thrust into a dangerous field assignment as he uncovers a pattern in terrorist communication that launches him into the center of a dangerous gambit.

name: Lonesome Dove
details: Two former Texas Rangers renew their spirit of adventure as they and several other residents of a small Texas town join a cattle drive to the Montana Territory.

name: Boston Legal
details: Boston Legal is a spin-off of the long-running David E. Kelley series The Practice (1997), following the exploits of former Practice character Alan Shore (James Spader) at the legal firm of Crane, Poole, and Schmidt.

name: Utopia
details: After a group of people, who meet online, discover a bizarre graphic novel which seems to hold mysterious answers, they find themselves being tracked down by a merciless organization known merely as 'The Network'.

name: The Adventures of Sherlock Holmes
details: Sherlock Holmes and Dr Watson solve the mysteries of copper beeches, a Greek interpreter, the Norwood builder, a resident patient, the red-headed league, and one final problem.

name: Carnivàle
details: During the Great Depression, an Oklahoma farm boy and a charismatic minister learn that they are key players in a proxy war being fought between Heaven and Hell.

name: Castlevania
details: A vampire hunter fights to save a besieged city from an army of otherworldly creatures controlled by Dracula.

name: True Blood
details: Telepathic waitress Sookie Stackhouse encounters a strange new supernatural world when she meets the mysterious Bill Compton, a southern Louisiana gentleman and vampire.
